OL,3,CMurder trial couple 'called the police
OL,4,Con each other in 30-year period'
OL,6,FA couple at the centre of a murder
OL,7,Ftrial called the police on each other
OL,8,Fmore than a dozen times over the past
OL,9,F30 years, complaining of physical
OL,10,Fviolence, theft and criminal damage.
OL,12,FChristine Rawle, 70, is on trial for
OL,13,Fthe alleged murder of Ian Rawle at
OL,14,Ftheir north Devon home.
OL,16,FThe court heard she accused her
OL,17,Fhusband of hitting her with a shovel;
OL,18,Fpuncturing her car tyres; stealing her
OL,19,Ftax disc; throwing a statue through a
OL,20,Fglass door; urinating into a drawer
OL,21,Fand injuring her son with an ashtray.
