OL,6,FIan Rawle, while on the phone to the
OL,7,Fpolice, said his wife stabbed him in
OL,8,Fthe chest and neck; placed a hosepipe
OL,9,Fthrough her sunroof and filled the car
OL,10,Fwith water; broke into his house and
OL,11,Fstole personal items; and hit him with
OL,12,Fa riding crop.
OL,14,FJurors at Exeter Crown Court, where
OL,15,FMrs Rawle is on trial for allegedly
OL,16,Fmurdering Mr Rawle, heard an extensive
OL,17,Flist of the couple's police complaints
OL,18,Fagainst each other, dating back to
OL,19,F1992.
