OL,6,F"He was becoming progressively
OL,7,Ffrustrated as he was giving me tasks
OL,8,Fwhich were beyond what I was able to
OL,9,Fachieve.
OL,11,F"He got a metal ruler and hit me
OL,12,Faround the head with it. It was
OL,13,Fpainful and unjustified."
OL,15,FTom Rawle told the court Ian Rawle
OL,16,Fthen picked up a hot ashtray and threw
OL,17,Fit at him.
OL,19,F"He had a set of heavy garden gloves,"
OL,20,Fhe said.
