OL,6,F"I was wearing shorts and a T-shirt.
OL,7,FHe threw the ashtray directly at me
OL,8,Fand it struck me in the leg. It left
OL,9,Fme with a severe circular burn on my
OL,10,Fleg. I was crying.
OL,12,F"He played it down and said he didn't
OL,13,Fmean it in a malicious way, but he
OL,14,Fabsolutely did. It wasn't an accident."
OL,16,FHe said his mother tried to protect
OL,17,Fhim and a fight broke out. Tom told
OL,18,Fthe court Ian Rawle punched his mother
OL,19,F"in the side of the face."
